{"lemma":"مُحَرَّمٌ","slug":"مُحَرَّمٌ","root":"ح.ر.م","root_slug":"ح-ر-م","root_link":"/words/roots/ح-ر-م","pos":"ADJ","pos_camel":"adj","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"مُحَرَّم","root":"حرم","pos":"N","occurrence_count":4},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["adj","name"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":2},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n7782"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%85%D9%8F%D8%AD%D9%8E%D8%B1%D9%8E%D9%91%D9%85%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adj","gloss":"forbidden"},{"pos":"name","gloss":"Muharram (the first month of the Islamic calendar, when many Islamic communities hold a festival commemorating the deaths of the grandsons of Muhammad)"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Derived from the passive participle of حَرَّمَ (ḥarrama, “to forbid”); compare حَرَام (ḥarām, “forbidden”).\n\nFrom الْمُحَرَّم (al-muḥarram, “the forbidden”), from الشَّهْر الْمُحَرَّم (aš-šahr al-muḥarram), literally \"the forbidden month\", for being one of the four months in which Arabs forbade fighting, a tradition continued in Islam. The month is of special importance for Shia Muslims, for being the month in which the Battle of Karbala occurred."},"ipa":["/mu.ħar.ram/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n7782","headword_ar":"مُحَرَّمٌ","root":"Hrm","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Forbidden, prohibited,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"made un lawful:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"made,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pronounced, sacred,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in violable,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"entitled to reverence"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"respect"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"honour"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. It is said in a trad.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^amaA Ealimota A^an~a AlS~uwrapa","text_ar":"اَمَا عَلِمْتَ اَنَّ الصُّورَةَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muHar~amapu","text_ar":"مُحَرَّمَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e. ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Knowest thou not that the face is"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"forbidden to be beaten?"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that it has a title to reverence"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"respect"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"honour?"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmuHar~amu","text_ar":"المُحَرَّمُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The first of the months"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K, * TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the year"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the Arabs"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"since the age of pagan ism"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (TA;) the article"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al","text_ar":"ال"},{"kind":"text","text":"being prefixed because it is originally an epithet; but accord. to some, it is not prefixed to the name of any other month; or, accord. to some, it may be prefixed to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sfr","text_ar":"صفر"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$w~Al","text_ar":"شوّال"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb:) and ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the age of paganism, the seventh month, also called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ahoru A@ll~`hi AlA^aSab~u","text_ar":"شَهْرُ ا@للّٰهِ الاَصَبُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA.) ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlASb~","text_ar":"الاصبّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"being app. a dial. var. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^aSam~u","text_ar":"الاَصَمُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajabN","text_ar":"رَجَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; [for] Az says, the Arabs used to call the month of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajab","text_ar":"رَجَب"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the age of paganism,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^aSam~u","text_ar":"الاَصَمُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmuHar~amu","text_ar":"المُحَرَّمُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and he cites the saying of a poet,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"A^aqamonaA bihaA $ahoraYo rabiyEK kilaAhumaA\n                      \n                     \n                        wa$ahoraYo jumaAdaY waA@sotaHal~uwA AlmuHar~amaA"},{"kind":"page_break","n":557},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"We stayed in it during the two months of Rabeea, both of them, and the two months of Jumádà; and they made El-Moharram to be profane;"},{"kind":"text","text":"app. by postponing it, as the pagan Arabs often did]: the Arabs called it thus because they did not allow fighting in it [unless they had postponed it]: (TA:) the pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muHar~amaAtN","text_ar":"مُحَرَّمَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maHaArimu","text_ar":"مَحَارِمُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maHaAriymu","text_ar":"مَحَارِيمُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.) ―         -b3-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaramN","text_ar":"حَرَمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"—"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muHar~amN","text_ar":"مُحَرَّمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"applied to a camel means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Refractory,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"untractable:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) [or,] thus applied, [like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaruwDN","text_ar":"عَرُوضٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", q. v.,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"submissive in the middle part,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[but]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"difficult to be turned about,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stubborn in the head,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"when turned about:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K: [in the CK,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al*~aluwlu AlwasaTu","text_ar":"الذَّلُولُ الوَسَطُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is erroneously put for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al*~aluwlu AlwasaTi","text_ar":"الذَّلُولُ الوَسَطِ"},{"kind":"text","text":": in my MS. copy of the K,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al*~aluwlu","text_ar":"الذَّلُولُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlwasT","text_ar":"الوَسط"},{"kind":"text","text":":]) and with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":"a she-camel"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"not broken, or not trained:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"not yet completely broken or trained:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muHar~amapu AlZ~ahori","text_ar":"مُحَرَّمَةُ الظَّهْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"a she-camel that is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"refractory,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"untractable; not broken, or not trained:"},{"kind":"text","text":"in this sense heard by Az from the Arabs. (TA.) ―         -b4-  (tropical:)  A skin"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"not tanned:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"not completely tanned:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tanned, but not made soft, and not thoroughly done."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b5-  (tropical:)  A"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"new"},{"kind":"text","text":"whip: (K:) or a whip"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"not yet made soft."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, TA.) ―         -b6-  (tropical:)  An Arab of the desert"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rude in nature"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"disposition, chaste in speech, that has not mixed with people of the towns or villages."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b7-  (assumed tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"part"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the nose"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that is soft in the hand."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.)"}],"source_refs":["Msb","TA","K","S"]}]},"classical_definitions":{"source":"hawramani","url":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/%D9%85%D8%AD%D8%B1%D9%85/","headword_ar":"محرم","entries":[{"lexicon_id":"dictionary_18","lexicon_en":"Al-Sharīf al-Jurjānī, Kitāb al-Taʿrīfāt (d. 1413 CE)","lexicon_ar":"كتاب التعريفات للشريف الجرجاني","permalink":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/?p=23592#952d09","body_html":"<span>المحرم: ما ثبت النهي فيه بلا عارض، وحكمه الثواب بالترك لله تعالى، والعقاب بالفعل والكفر بالاستحلال، في المتفق.</span>"}]}}